            <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:#00CCCC;font-family">Idly</h2>

            <img style="padding-left:250px;width:350px;height:300px" src="https://i.pinimg.com/564x/81/62/ab/8162abad260677b33816d3b47371dcf9.jpg" alt="idly">
            <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
            <ul>
                <ul>
                    <li>1 cup of idly rice.</li>
                    <li> 1/4 cup of urad dal (split black gram).</li>
                    <li> Salt to taste.</li>
                </ul>

            </ul>


            <h3>Process:</h3>
            <ul>
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Wash and Soak:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li>Wash the rice and urad dal separately under running water until the water runs clear.</li>
                <li>Soak the rice, urad dal in separate bowls with enough water for 4-6 hours or overnight.</li>
                <br />

                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Drain and Grind:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li>Drain the soaked urad dal and rice.</li>
                <li>In a grinder or blender, grind the urad dal with enough water to make a smooth and fluffy batter.</li>
                <li> It should take about 15-20 minutes of grinding. The consistency should be similar to whipped cream.</li>
                <li>Transfer the urad dal batter to a large mixing bowl.</li>
                <br />
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Grind Rice:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li> Grind the soaked rice with enough water to make a smooth batter.</li>
                <li> The consistency should be similar to pancake batter.</li>
                <li>Combine the rice batter with the urad dal batter in the mixing bowl.</li>
                <br />
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Add Salt and Fermentation: </li></b>
                <br />
                <li> Add salt to the batter and mix well.</li>
                <li> Allow the batter to ferment for 6-8 hours or overnight in a warm place. During fermentation, the batter will rise and become slightly airy.</li>
                <br />
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Prepare Idly Molds:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li>Grease the idly molds with a little oil or use idly stand liners to prevent sticking.</li>
                <br />
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Fill the Molds:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li>Pour the fermented batter into the idly molds, filling each mold about 3/4 full.</li>
                <br />

                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Steam Idlys:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li>Heat water in the idly steamer or a large steaming pot.</li>
                <li>Place the filled idly molds in the steamer and steam for about 10-15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of an idly comes out clean.</li>
                <br />
                <br />

                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Remove and Serve:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li>Once done, remove the idly molds from the steamer and let them cool for a minute.</li>
                <li>Use a spoon to gently remove the idlys from the molds.</li>
                <br />
                <br />

                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:#66CC00">Serve Hot:</li></b>
                <br />
                <li>Serve the idlys hot with coconut chutney, sambar, or your favorite accompaniments.</li>
                <br />
                <h3>Enjoy your homemade idlys!</h3>
